contrast-enhanced multidetector row CT in a porcine model. <em>Radiology</em>2004;231:697–701.</div><div class="external-links"><div class="core-xlink-crossref"><a href="https://doi.org/10.1148/radiol.2313030132">Crossref</a></div><div class="core-xlink-pubmed"><a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/15118118/">PubMed</a></div><div class="core-xlink-google-scholar"><a href="https://scholar.google.com/scholar_lookup?title=Radiology&amp;publication_year=2004&amp;pages=697&amp;doi=10.1148%2Fradiol.2313030132&amp;pmid=15118118">Google Scholar</a></div></div></div></div></div></div></section></div></section></div><div class="core-collateral" role="dialog" aria-modal="true"><div id="core-collateral-info" data-active-pane="false"><header><h2><i class="icon-info" aria-hidden="true"></i>Information &amp; Authors</h2></header><section id="tab-information" role="tabpanel"><h3>Information</h3><section class="core-self-citation"><h4>Published In</h4><div class="core-journal-presentation">



        
        <div class="cover-image flat d-flex justify-content-center flex-column"><div data-is-viewable="" class="cover-image__image"><a href="/toc/radiographics/26/4" title="Go to RadioGraphics " class="d-block"><img src="/cms/10.1148/radiographics.2006.26.issue-4/asset/1463f6a5-6b14-3f6a-56b1-63f6a556b146/cover.jpg" alt="Go to RadioGraphics " loading="lazy"/></a></div></div>
<div class="core-journal-description"><div property="isPartOf" typeof="Periodical"><span property="name">RadioGraphics</span></div><div class="core-enumeration"><span property="isPartOf" typeof="PublicationVolume">Volume <span property="volumeNumber">26</span></span> • <span property="isPartOf" typeof="PublicationIssue">Number <span property="issueNumber">4</span></span> • <span property="datePublished">Jul 1 2006</span></div><div class="core-pagination"><span class="heading">Pages</span>: <span class="content"><span property="pageStart">963</span> - <span property="pageEnd">978</span></span></div><div class="core-pmid"><span class="heading">PubMed</span>: <a class="content" href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/16844926/" property="sameAs" target="_blank" title="Link to PubMed">16844926</a></div></div></div></section><section class="core-copyright"><h4>Copyright</h4><div role="paragraph">© RSNA, 2006.</div></section><section class="core-history"><h4>History</h4><div><b class="core-label">Published online</b>: Jul 1 2006</div></section><section class="core-permissions"><h4>Permissions</h4><div>Request permissions for this article.</div><div><a class="btn" href="https://marketplace.copyright.com/rs-ui-web/mp/search/all/10.1148%2Frg.264055709">Request Permissions</a></div></section><section property="keywords"><h4>Keywords</h4><ol><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=ECG+%3D+electrocardiography&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">ECG = electrocardiography</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=MIP+%3D+maximum+intensity+projection&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">MIP = maximum intensity projection</a></li><li><a href="/action/doSearch?AllField=3D+%3D+three-dimensional&amp;stemming=yes&amp;publication=radiographics" alt="Search on this keyword" rel="nofollow">3D = three-dimensional</a></li></ol></section><section class="core-article-notes"><h4>Notes</h4><div role="paragraph">The use of multidetector CT to obtain detailed information about the presence and extent of coronary artery disease in emergency department patients with acute chest pain is discussed with a view toward improving initial triage and management.</div></section></section><section id="tab-contributors" role="tabpanel"><h3>Authors</h3><section class="core-authors"><h4>Affiliations</h4><div id="con1" property="author" typeof="Person"><div class="heading"><span property="givenName">Udo</span> <span property="familyName">Hoffmann</span>, <span property="honorificSuffix">MD</span></div><div class="content"><div class="affiliations"><div property="affiliation" typeof="Organization"><span property="name">From the Departments of Radiology (U.H., A.J.P., R.C.C., S.A., M.F., F.M., U.S., T.J.B.) and Emergency Medicine (J.T.N.), Massachusetts General Hospital, 165 Charles River Plaza, Suite 400, Boston, MA 02114; and Harvard School of Public Health, Boston, Mass (U.H.). Received April 29, 2005; revision requested June 9 and received August 31; accepted October 13. All authors have no financial relationships to disclose.</span></div></div><div class="core-author-link"><a href="/authored-by/Hoffmann/Udo" rel="nofollow">View all articles by this author</a></div></div></div><div id="con2" property="author" typeof="Person"><div class="heading"><span property="givenName">Antonio J.</span> <span property="familyName">Pena</span>, <span property="honorificSuffix">MD</span></div><div class="content"><div class="affiliations"><div property="affiliation" typeof="Organization"><span property="name">From the Departments of Radiology (U.H., A.J.P., R.C.C., S.A., M.F., F.M., U.S., T.J.B.) and Emergency Medicine (J.T.N.), Massachusetts General Hospital, 165 Charles River Plaza, Suite 400, Boston, MA 02114; and Harvard School of Public Health, Boston, Mass (U.H.). Received April 29, 2005; revision requested June 9 and received August 31; accepted October 13. All authors